    The variable price with the value 9.99 belongs to the float data type, which represents floating-point numbers      (decimal numbers).


Q9. Printing a Variable:
                To print the value of the variable name, we can use the print() function:

             python
            
           name = "sindhu shekhar"
              print(name)  # Output: sindhu shekhar
              
              
Q10. Extracting a Substring:
To extract the substring "World" from the given string "Hello, World!", we can use string slicing:

          python
       
           s = "Hello, World!"
          substring = s[7:12]
           print(substring)  # Output: World
           
           
Q11. Declaring a Boolean Variable:
To declare a variable named is_student and assign it a boolean value (e.g., True if i am a student, False otherwise):

       python
        
           is_student = True  # Change to False if not a student
